.TH RAPTD 1 "February 2026" "rapt 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
raptd \- daemon for installing R packages via apt
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B raptd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B raptd
is a minimal C daemon that listens on a Unix socket and executes
apt\-get commands on behalf of R sessions. It bridges R's
.BR install.packages ()
to apt for binary R package installation from the r2u repository.
.PP
The daemon listens on
.I /run/raptd.sock
and accepts newline\-delimited commands:
.TP
.BI install " pkg1 [pkg2 ...]"
Install one or more R packages via apt\-get.
.TP
.BI remove " pkg1 [pkg2 ...]"
Remove one or more R packages via apt\-get.
.PP
Package names are mapped from R names to Debian names
(e.g., dplyr becomes r\-cran\-dplyr).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /run/raptd.sock
Unix domain socket for client communication.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR apt\-get (8),
.BR systemd (1)
